        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>– Sensitivity: Our aim here is to reveal whether H2S is present or not in Neptune's stratosphere. Thus, needed sensitivity is to detect H2S with 3-sigma rms noise level even if its abundance is expected lower limit. As a lower limit abundance of H2S, we assume [H2S]/[CO] value as 0.5%, which is several times lower than typical S/O value of small solar system bodies, 2%. The spectral line width of H2S is expected to be ~3MHz, derived by pressure broadening above 1mbar level. To derive the H2S vertical distribution, emission line has to be resolved. Therefore, needed frequency resolution becomes about 0.5MHz. To decrease the beam dilution effect, here we use 1” synthesis beam size, which is relatively smaller than Neptune's disk, 2”.2. Then, we estimated the intensity of various H2S transitions using 1-D radiative transfer calculation. Taking into account the sensitivity of each bands and atmospheric transparency, we selected H2S 3(3,0)-3(2,1) transition at 300.506GHz. As a result, H2S intensity assuming even its lower limit abundance was derived as 261mK in antenna temperature scale. Since there are no bright lines around 300GHz, rms noise level calculated by ALMA OT can be achievable. H2CS 9(1,8)-8(1,7) line at 313.717 GHz, which can be observed simultaneously in the other sideband, is expected to be stronger than H2S assuming the same abundance as H2S. Therefore, observation time is simply calculated by H2S intensity. In summary, we request 40 miniutes for total observation time to achieve 87mK rms noise level with 1” spatial distribution and 0.488 MHz frequency resolution to achieve the 3-sigma detection of H2S even if its abundance is at lower limit. 
Please note that although we selected 0.244MHz resolution, we calculated observation time using 0.488 MHz resolution.
– Imaging: Since our aim here is not to map the spatial distribution of H2S, we have no specific request here.
– Correlator setup: 
As mentioned above, please set two spectral window at 300.506GHz forH2S and 313.717GHz for H2CS. Since their expected linewidth is not so wide, we use 500MHz bandwidth with 0.122 MHz resolution mode. We choose several times higher frequency resolution because in case of detection with high-S/N, we can derive detailed vertical distribution. 
– Calibration: 
No special request.
– Bandpass accuracy: 
No special request because expected linewidth is narrow. 
– Scheduling/time constraints:
No special request.
– Data rate: 
Since no error message was appeared on OT, data rate is expected to be lower than 6MB/s.
– Special constraints on standard observing modes:
No special request.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
